comments.body:
Reading this now, I think I'd prefer to keep this constructor private and add a couple of static factory methods:

```scala
object LedgerIdRequirement {
  val none = LedgerIdRequirement(None)

  def matching(ledgerId: String) = LedgerIdRequirement(Some(ledgerId))

  @deprecated("Use static factory methods", "1.3.0")
  def apply(ledgerId: String, enabled: Boolean): LedgerIdRequirement =
    if (enabled) matching(ledgerId) else none
}
```
